File actions: 
C-x C-f : find a file

Emacs actions:
C-x C-+ or C-- : zoom in/out
C-x C-c : Close Emacs
C-x C-h : show global keybinding
C-x t   : show Emacs tutorial
C-g     : stop executing current command if Emacs not responding

Buffer action:
C-x C-s : save buffer
C-x C-b : show list of available buffers
C-x b: swith to buffer
C-x k: kill current b

C-x u : undo changes
C-k	: Kill from the cursor position to end of line
M-k	: Kill to the end of the current sentence


Windows actions:
C-x 1 : delete all windows except of one base

Dired(file tree)
M-x dired : open file tree


Counsel:
C-j/k in a list: go to next/prev line in a list
C-x b : swith to buffer
C-x C-b : find file
C-l, TAB or enter to select buffer/command/file under the selected line
C-d : delete the current selected buffer(if before we call C-x b to swith buffer or M-x and etc)
Alt-o in the minibufer list(if before we call C-x b to swith buffer or M-x and etc) to show available actions, such as copy command/file name in the list
